Shrinkage through prior specification will be used as a method for mitigating issues associated with multiplicity. Additionally, only first-order interactions will be considered, which implicitly assumes all higher order interactions are set to zero. Specifically, for the subgroup treatment effects, a revised linear predictor will be introduced from the earlier specification in the “Primary, secondary and exploratory outcomes” section: 
